source_id: STP1023-EB-Zirconium in the Nuclear Industry_8th Volume_009_chunk8
evidence_span: ABSTRACT: The influence of the composition of Zircaloy-type alloys...
composition_raw: tin: 0.2 to 1.7%; iron: 0.05 to 0.53%; chromium: 0.04 to 1.05%; nickel: 0.003 to 0.046%; oxygen, carbon, silicon, phosphorus varied
process_step: conventional fabrication with intermediate beta quench followed by working and annealing in upper alpha-range
conditions: pressurized water at 350°C (380-840 days); high pressure steam at 400°C (180-397 days)
corrosion_data: time to transition increases with decreasing tin and carbon, increasing silicon; post-transition rate decreases with same factors

extra_properties.corrosion_environment: pressurized water and high pressure steam
extra_properties.precipitate_characterization: SEM and TEM examination of intermetallic precipitates
extra_properties.Fe_Cr_effect: accelerated corrosion at Fe+Cr ≤ 0.15%, especially in steam; high Cr/Fe ratios result in high corrosion
extra_properties.element_effects: oxygen and phosphorus showed no influence in studied range
